ABUJA – As the world grapples with the emergence of the coronavirus, President Muhammadu Buhari has extended his good wishes to President Xi Jinping and citizens of the People’s Republic of China. Buhari described the current challenge as a trying time for China, lauding it for efforts to contain the spread of the coronavirus, especially its collaboration with international agencies and other countries on the matter. President Buhari noted that China has been exceptionally supportive of Nigeria and Africa, and even more so in recent years; therefore, it is important to let China know that Nigeria and her citizens are also standing by them during this outbreak. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network Buhari, who spoke through his media aide, Femi Adesina on Sunday, said with all the efforts being put in, we know that it is only a matter of time before this nightmare passes. The Nigerian President used the opportunity to thank Nigerians for their hospitality towards the Chinese nationals in our midst, and for not letting the coronavirus outbreak create any disturbance or disrupt the peaceful coexistence between us and them. He prayed that God will comfort the Chinese and others who have already lost family members and loved ones to the disease.